8  |  DISCOVERY QUESTIONS — Surface MariApps weaknesses naturally

Ask without naming MariApps. Expose gaps that favour AMOS™.

•	How long has the vendor been operating, and can they point to customers live for more than 10–15 years in environments similar in complexity to yours?
•	Is the platform purpose-built for asset management and compliance, or is it a broader ERP that includes those as modules?
•	Do maintenance, compliance, performance, and governance data all live in one database — or require integration between separate products?
•	Who owns the software vendor — and could any commercial relationship between the vendor's parent and competing operators affect you?
•	Where is the product developed, and how does that affect data sovereignty, support responsiveness, and roadmap ownership?
•	If you need enterprise governance reporting across multiple entities and regions — have you seen it demonstrated at that scale?
•	When the vendor says 'AI-powered' or 'digital twin' — what specific operational decisions does that enable today, and what data is it trained on?
•	What is your current three-way invoice match rate — and what does a failed match cost in investigation time?
•	How much procurement spend variance do you carry per quarter — and can you see it in real time at the point of approval?
•	Can you speak to a reference customer at your fleet size and regulatory complexity, live for 5+ years?

